modules.description: This module provides functions to manipulate and expand source code positions and file paths during PPX rewriting. It handles lexing positions by lifting them into expressions or string literals and resolves relative file paths based on a configured directory. Useful for implementing custom syntax extensions that need to track or modify source locations and file references.

This module provides functions to obtain and manipulate source code position information, such as file name, line number, and character offsets. It works with the `position` record type, which captures location details from the lexer. Concrete use cases include tracking error locations during parsing or logging precise source positions for debugging and tooling.
